Minesweeper
===========

This is a minimal version of minesweeper written in C with SDL2.
It currently doesn't draw text, so it uses colors to display the tiles.

Tile colors
-----------
Unknown tile	- Gray
Flagged		- Yellow
Mine		- Black
Empty		- Dark gray
1 Mine		- Blue
2 Mines		- Green
3 Mines		- Red
4 Mines		- Dark blue
5 Mines		- Dark red
6 Mines		- Cyan
7 Mines		- Purple
8 Mines		- Light gray
9 Mines :)	- White

Flags
-----
-d <w> <h>	Specify minefield dimensions
-h 		Prints usage
-m <n>		Specify number of mines

Building
--------
Run `make` to build and run `make install` (may require root) to install.

